2364
01:44:04,110 --> 01:44:06,660
The choice that I'm
referring to is spirulina,

2365
01:44:06,660 --> 01:44:09,040
which is actually a form of algae.

2366
01:44:09,040 --> 01:44:12,070
Years ago, I think when I
first heard about spirulina,

2367
01:44:12,070 --> 01:44:14,937
it sounded very much of the kind of 1970s,

2368
01:44:14,937 --> 01:44:17,290
80s health food store variety.

2369
01:44:17,290 --> 01:44:19,960
It seemed really kind
of mystical and wacky,

2370
01:44:19,960 --> 01:44:22,450
but actually now there are
some really nice studies

2371
01:44:22,450 --> 01:44:25,240
and some data, and also an
understanding of the mechanism

2372
01:44:25,240 --> 01:44:28,010
by which spirulina can have potent effects

2373
01:44:28,010 --> 01:44:29,930
in reducing what's called rhinitis,

2374
01:44:29,930 --> 01:44:33,440
which is a fancy word for
congestion of the nose

2375
01:44:33,440 --> 01:44:34,820
and an inflammation of the nose.

2376
01:44:34,820 --> 01:44:39,820
Basically, anytime you hear
a word that includes "itis,"

2377
01:44:39,860 --> 01:44:41,850
at least if it's in the
medical or health context,

2378
01:44:41,850 --> 01:44:44,200
it generally means
inflammation of some tissue.

2379
01:44:45,490 --> 01:44:48,650
So rhinitis just being
inflammation of the nasal passages,

2380
01:44:48,650 --> 01:44:50,530
but that's one of the most
uncomfortable symptoms

2381
01:44:50,530 --> 01:44:52,080
of any kind of infection.

2382
01:44:52,080 --> 01:44:54,330
So there are two studies
I'd like to highlight

2383
01:44:54,330 --> 01:44:55,200
just very quickly.

2384
01:44:55,200 --> 01:44:58,220
One is the effects of
spirulina on allergic rhinitis.

2385
01:44:58,220 --> 01:45:00,020
And the other is a clinical comparison

2386
01:45:00,020 --> 01:45:01,970
to the efficacy of spirulina platensis,

2387
01:45:05,360 --> 01:45:06,802
that's a technical name,

2388
01:45:06,802 --> 01:45:10,630
and cetirizine for the
treatment of allergic rhinitis.

2389
01:45:10,630 --> 01:45:13,590
These looked at humans, so
this is not a mouse study,

2390
01:45:13,590 --> 01:45:14,890
this is a study on humans.

2391
01:45:16,210 --> 01:45:18,820
Both sexes, so males and females.

2392
01:45:18,820 --> 01:45:22,376
In one case, looking at 100
plus subjects, 129 subjects.

2393
01:45:22,376 --> 01:45:24,700
The other, 65 subjects, so
decent number of subjects,

2394
01:45:24,700 --> 01:45:27,480
randomized trial, double blind.

2395
01:45:27,480 --> 01:45:32,480
Both cases saw significant
decreases in nasal obstruction,

2396
01:45:33,090 --> 01:45:36,233
improved ability to smell, improved sleep,

2397
01:45:37,430 --> 01:45:42,313
daily working inflammatory
cytokines were reduced as well,

2398
01:45:43,440 --> 01:45:44,460
reduction in nasal itching,

2399
01:45:44,460 --> 01:45:46,340
all the stuff that you'd
like to experience,

2400
01:45:46,340 --> 01:45:49,340
I can imagine, after taking two grams,

2401
01:45:49,340 --> 01:45:52,770
two grams, not milligrams,
but two grams of spirulina.

2402
01:45:52,770 --> 01:45:55,210
Sometimes had to be
taken for a short while

2403
01:45:55,210 --> 01:45:56,760
before the effect kicked in.

2404
01:45:56,760 --> 01:45:59,480
So, that's pretty impressive, I would say,

2405
01:45:59,480 --> 01:46:01,320
but it doesn't really speak to mechanism,

2406
01:46:01,320 --> 01:46:05,240
but in exploring the underlying
mechanisms for spirulina's

2407
01:46:05,240 --> 01:46:08,280
effects on reducing rhinitis,

2408
01:46:08,280 --> 01:46:12,560
it's interesting to find that
spirulina actually can inhibit

2409
01:46:12,560 --> 01:46:15,570
the formation and/or activity of so-called

2410
01:46:15,570 --> 01:46:19,550
histaminergic mast cells,
M-A-S-T, mast cells.

2411
01:46:19,550 --> 01:46:21,620
We haven't talked a lot about mast cells,

2412
01:46:21,620 --> 01:46:23,800
but they are a very interesting cell type

2413
01:46:23,800 --> 01:46:25,610
in the immune response.

2414
01:46:25,610 --> 01:46:29,510
Essentially what they are, are
little packets of histamine.

2415
01:46:29,510 --> 01:46:34,510
And when we have some sort
of injury or irritant rather

2416
01:46:36,970 --> 01:46:40,290
to the skin, so a mosquito
bite, for instance,

2417
01:46:40,290 --> 01:46:42,143
or poison oak or poison ivy,

2418
01:46:43,470 --> 01:46:44,860
something that causes an itch

2419
01:46:44,860 --> 01:46:47,080
or something that causes
inflammation internally,

2420
01:46:47,080 --> 01:46:48,590
doesn't just have to be on the skin,

2421
01:46:48,590 --> 01:46:51,690
these mast are these little
bubbles that contain histamine

2422
01:46:51,690 --> 01:46:53,850
that go to that site [hissing],

2423
01:46:53,850 --> 01:46:56,200
and release their histaminergic contents

2424
01:46:56,200 --> 01:47:00,270
and cause swelling and
inflammation of whatever cells

2425
01:47:00,270 --> 01:47:01,403
are affected locally.

2426
01:47:02,520 --> 01:47:04,530
You might think, well, why
would I want to have a mechanism

2427
01:47:04,530 --> 01:47:06,760
in my body that would cause
swelling and inflammation?

2428
01:47:06,760 --> 01:47:11,140
Ah, well then those cells in
turn send out cytokine signals

2429
01:47:11,140 --> 01:47:15,010
that recruit the very cell
types that we were talking about

2430
01:47:15,010 --> 01:47:17,640
way back at the beginning of the episode,

2431
01:47:17,640 --> 01:47:19,470
the cells that are characteristics

2432
01:47:19,470 --> 01:47:21,730
of the innate immune system that come in,

2433
01:47:21,730 --> 01:47:24,290
the macrophages and the
other types of cells

2434
01:47:24,290 --> 01:47:26,960
that will come in and gobble
up the foreign invaders

2435
01:47:26,960 --> 01:47:29,860
or will help sequester and move away,

2436
01:47:29,860 --> 01:47:34,040
say the poison from a bite
or from whatever irritant.

2437
01:47:34,040 --> 01:47:36,910
Again, it doesn't just have
to be at the skin surface.

2438
01:47:36,910 --> 01:47:40,160
I'm describing an example of
at the skin, for instance,

2439
01:47:40,160 --> 01:47:43,180
if you've ever had hives of any kind,

2440
01:47:43,180 --> 01:47:47,060
that almost certainly involved mast cells.

2441
01:47:47,060 --> 01:47:51,640
So, and when you take an
anti-histamine in order to deal

2442
01:47:51,640 --> 01:47:53,540
with seasonal allergies, for instance,

2443
01:47:56,014 --> 01:47:57,970
you're taking a compound that's reducing

2444
01:47:57,970 --> 01:47:59,690
histamines in mast cells.

2445
01:47:59,690 --> 01:48:02,750
And spirulina has also been
